For those of you hat don't know, we had a puppy for about 2 weeks two weeks ago and took him back to the shelter. It was a no kill sheler and he was 4 months old, so i'm sure he has already been adopted by now. He was such a handful. We live in an apartment and it wasn't far because he was cooped up in his crate a lot during the day. I came home and let him out a lot, but I always felt guilty...like I wasn't doing enough. I feel worse because he was so smart. He learned quickly how to sleep through the night and how to not go in the house. Problem was, I was taking him out like 20 times a day. 
often i think i was the right choice for everyone. David was miserable and stressed out just coming home. I was always running around, trying to make sure the puppy got let out enough, got enough attention...etc...while balancing my internship and schoolwork. David and I had no time for each other. We couldn' get through a 30 minute tv show because the puppy was always needing something. Not having a backyard is terrible. 
But other times, i feel so horrible about it. School is ending in a month, and if I had waited...I would finally have enough time for the puppy. He was such a quick learner, things might have gotten better if we gave it more time. We jus had no idea how hard it would be in an apartment to make it work, especially because we are not the type to just crate the dog all the time. I sometimes wish we had given it more time, though I know that would have made it harder if we decided to take him back...plus we wanted to give him back while he was still young enough to be appealing to families. 
it still hurts, I really loved him. I'm sure the timing was wrong, i just wish I was 100% certain it wouldn't have gotten better.
I hate feeling sad.

So here's my situation. For my degree program, I need to do an internship. I have three that I got replies from (not a paid internship, btw...volunteer) One is this county soil and conservation education program, the second is an organization that raises money for head start and early education programs, and the third is United Way.

I met with the environmental one and LOVED the lady i'd be working with. Pros: Everything is casual. Pretty lax schedule except for planned events. VERY nice people. A cause I believe in.
Cons: Outside of actual events where we are working with the public, i'm just going to be playing it by ear....she'll be finding me stuff to do. I feel nervous since it's not super structured I won't reach my 100 hour requirement. I'm bothered because she kind of pushed me into acepting before I got to explore my other two options.

The second one sent me a proposal online and it seems like i might learn more from them. Seems a bit for structured. Another cool cause where I'd get to work with kids. I'm worried bec ause I haven't met them in person so I don't know how strict and demanding its going to be. 

The third, I have an appointment on Tuesday for and have no idea how it's gonna go.

The question is: If i decide one of the other two option is better for me, is it wrong to pull out on the environmental thing? I would tell her that I've found something that will more meet my course requirements, but that I would still like to commit to helping with some of the events.  I feel bad that I already accepted...she kind of just start telling people I was volunteering there before I'd said I was when I was in the office...but it's not like i'd be leaving her completely high and dry.

Tell me what you guys think....this whole thing is kind of stressing me out. Thank you!

I'm feeling kinda ca-ca this morning. Not like, sick....but I woke up with a stuffy nose and a headache. So, I napped then had a test in psychology. I know I did really well, got an A...but I dont feel very proud. Because the majority of the class had failed the last two { I got Ds.} the prof. gave us a study guide. it had forty of the fifty questions on it, we just had to find the answers. So, i found em and I memorized em plus I looked up the words to make sure I understood em and reviewed my lecture notes {the last ten were from lectures} So, of course I did well, it was super easy to get the right answers. But, I can't really feel proud of the grade, ya know? Everyone I have said that to thinks i'm lame...but I like working for good grades. Easy As make me feel bad. 
My tummy feels yucky...I feel all around blah. Dont wanna work in two hours, but I feel bad calling in. Plus, money would be nice. 
The marine corps ball is in a week and i'm pretty excited aboutit. I still need to do a lot of shoppping, if anyone feels like coming along this weekend, i'd love the company!

and to think...i woke up from a nap 2 hours ago feeling lonely and sad...

And lastly. God Bless Tommy Byrd and his family...as well as all of the other soldiers and families that have experienced loss...
No matter where you stand on the war, keep the troops in your thoughts...
Keep all people effected by our occupancy in your thoughts..

I hate the dorms....

So, lots of drama tonight. 
I was sitting in my room talking on the phone to my friend. On the phone I said something inappropriate {told a not nice joke} anyway, my suitmate came in, said she overheard me, and flipped out on me cussing a storm! So, i went back into her room and apologized for offending her but said she had no right to come into my room and talk shit. She told me I have horrible character and I'm shit and blah blh blah....went fucking crazy. Now i'm going home this weekend and I dont feel safe about my stuff because we share a bahtroom and she has access to my room at all tiems. I spoke to an RA and the only thing I can do to guarantee safety {and not punch her face in} is to move out. So...i spent the past two hours packing and I move my shit somewhere { i dunno where yet or with whom} at 8 am tomorrow.
I was supposed to have a midterm tomorrow but I emailed the teacher to tell him the situation. I'm gonna go see him tomorrow to make sure I can take a make up. IT will be a harder test, but it was all I could do.
I fucking hate girl drama...hate it. Tomorrow will be hell but then i'll be done with it.
Anyway, gotta do homework then crash. Please remind me that going through this hell makes you stronger...

Today was so great......
So, my boyfriend Robert came up to visit around 2:00 and just seeing him standing there was so nice. You don't realize how long a week really is until you're in a long distance relationship with someone you care about this much. We were neckin' in public like teenagers, it was great. :) {oh wait, i am a teenager}
Then we walked for awhile and found an ALL YOU CAN EAT indian restaurant with some bomb ass food. I love indian and it's his favorite, so we went crazy with the eating. It was pretty inexpensive too! 
After that we went and saw The Forty Year Old Virgin, which was fuckin' hilarious. I loved it. 
All too soon he had to go back to tucson...but seeing him was definitely what I needed to get through the week. Today was just so nice because we both felt so in love; playing with eachother, carrying me everywhere, joking around, kissing continuously, being mushy, eating good food. Anyway, it was great. I feel so happy. 
Now I'm going to get ready to go dancing for my dance class with some girls I know. much love to alll yaaall.

So...what is going on...
This is my first weekend up in Tempe without going home. *gasp! SHOCK! AWWWE* Really, it hasn't been as bad as I anticipated. On friday afternoon I went up to Payson with my friend Jeanette and some of her friends for a camping trip with her church. Only we got horribly lost and didn't get there until 10:30 pm! But, there were cold burgers waiting and we sat around a campfire...it was ncie being out in the not so scorching weather. Saturday after breakfast we came back here and i did errands all day. Which include {but are not limited to} cleaning my room, orgaanizing my papers, doing laundry, and doing math homework. IT sucked, but atleast i felt accomplished.
This morning I woke up early and went to church for the first time in forever. Everyone at the Methodist church up here was super nice and the college group leader is even a social work major like me! I'm hoping to get involved in church stuff soon...it felt so good being back around normal people. Heh..
Now i'm sitting her anxiously waiting the arrival of my boyfriend! he's coming up to visit for the day and i'm super excited. No clue what we'll do, but ah well. I know we're going to lunch somewhere...yay.
Linden, i really miss you. When you were talking about childhoods in your last post it reminded me how much we went through growin' up......Me in first grade with my short lesbo hair...a very tramatic time for a young, undeveloped girl..atleast back then having your ears pierced meant you were female, nowadays you can't tell... :)
Derek's mom had a fro.  Muah :)
Anyway, i'm off to waste more time till the boyfriend arrives...

Your Personality Is
Idealist (NF)
You are a passionate, caring, and unique person. You are good at expressing yourself and sharing your ideals. You are the most compassionate of all types and connect with others easily. Your heart tends to rule you. You can't make decisions without considering feelings. You seek out other empathetic people to befriend. Truth and authenticity matters in your friendships. In love, you give everything you have to relationships. You fall in love easily. At work, you crave personal expression and meaning in your career. With others, you communicate well. You can spend all night talking with someone. As far as your looks go, you've likely taken the time to develop your own personal style. On weekends, you like to be with others. Charity work is also a favorite pastime of yours.
The Three Question Personality Test
You Are 60% Boyish and 40% Girlish
You are pretty evenly split down the middle - a total eunuch. Okay, kidding about the eunuch part. But you do get along with both sexes. You reject traditional gender roles. However, you don't actively fight them. You're just you. You don't try to be what people expect you to be.
How Boyish or Girlish Are You?
The Keys to Your Heart
You are attracted to those who are unbridled, untrammeled, and free. In love, you feel the most alive when your lover is creative and never lets you feel bored. You'd like to your lover to think you are loyal and faithful... that you'll never change. You would be forced to break up with someone who was insecure and in constant need of reassurance. Your ideal relationship is comforting. You crave a relationship where you always feel warmth and love. Your risk of cheating is zero. You care about society and morality. You would never break a commitment. You think of marriage as something precious. You'll treasure marriage and treat it as sacred. In this moment, you think of love as commitment. Love only works when both people are totally devoted.
What Are The Keys To Your Heart?
Your Ideal Relationship is Marriage
You've dated enough to know what you want. And that's marriage - with the right person. You're serious about settling down some time soon. Even if you haven't met the person you want to get hitched to!
What's Your Ideal Relationship?

SO! I went to the gym and as soon as I got there, I noticed everyone was evacuating because the fire alarm got pulled. I wanted to leave but instead waited around for 20 minutes till they let us back in. The cool part? I ran straight to the machines before the other bitches could...SUCKAS!
I did 45 minutes on the Eliptical machine with the incline at 9 { the highest is ten} and the resistance at 6. I did 5347 steps! MUAHAHA....then i went and weight lifted with my legs...THEN I rode my bike back to the dorm...THENNNN I took the stairs! I feel rippppppppped. hehe...i'm a dork.
Anyway, my sweat is drying and I feel yucko. Time for a shower, dinner, then homework. Much love!

Man...I dunno. 
I was stressed out this afternoon for a bunch of reasons, called my mom this afternoon and vented...now I feel better,but kind of drained. I dunno man, moving is hard. It all started because i got FUCKING PISSED that i had to buy this stupid 30 dollar remote control thingy for a religions class. College is just so expensive and right now it doesn't seem worth it. It's like i'm PAYING to be thrown into a situation where I have to always wear my shiny, happy face and hope to meet cool people. I'm PAYING to sit in a room and have some guy go over the same material I'm reading in a textbook. I'm PAYING for this "experience"...which so far doesn't seem so awesome. {yes yes, i know, it'll get better...only been here a month...it takes time...i'll meet cool people eventually...yadda yadda} I'm just sayin, i think some of you pima people have the right idea; doing college for cheap. I dunno, realistically I'm not paying too much in comparison to other people in college. but damn! Just seems like if i'm paying for it, i should be enjoying it more. GAH..plus, i have to go on a 30 minute bus ride to the social security office, get another social security card, and then go fill out a huge new hire packet. Not having a car out here is pretty crippling. 
AND! Can i please just say something to all yall bitches? 
Remember when you saw a kid with choppy black hair, spikes, chucks, and a skateboard and it meant they probably listened to angry white people music? A la Mudvayne, Slipknot, etc? WELL! nowadays you see a kid like that and then have a MY CHEMICAL ROMANCE shirt on....or something else whiny. AHHH where are the bad asses? 
sorry if you IM me and I don't respond....i forget to put up my message a lot.

Sooo...i was up till 2:30 last night studying for my Religions of the World exam. Intended on waking up super early to study more before the test at 9:40. Needless to say, I slept till about 8:40 {hehe} But, I just got done taking the exams and I'm pretty damn sure I ROCKED THAT BIATCH!
Now I have about an hour until my next class, and last class of the day; math. Believe it or not, I've totally stayed on top of my math assignments thus far. Considering how much I hate math, it's a little bit of a suprise.

All you computer geniuses out there, ATTENTION!! 
I have a new Dell, with windows XP. Well, outta no where it started acting up alot. When it loads after you turn it on, the chimey sound is all crackly and skippy. Then, when I play a CD with Windows MEdia, it always starts out all crackly and skippy.....then if I try to do something {like access email} is starts playing slow and crackly again. It's almost like i'm trying to do too many things at once, when i'm only doing super simple things. Any advice??

A week before today will be Robert and I's 3 month anniversary. {tee hee hee} I love him so much. We just got off the phone and, like always, we couldn't talk long at all { I hate his work schedule} But, before hanging up he madea point to tell me how important to him our relationship is and how sorry he is that this distance makes it difficult to feel as connected to each other as we usually are. Well, needless to say...he really put a smile on my face. 
So Murphy, I heard you met the boyfriend...how random is that? :)

Welp, i'm out. time for a shower since I have time. {yes, be proud, i went to my last class in PJ's and a santa rita drama t-shirt}

In reply to Carrie's post, I was INSPIRED to post on my ever faithful livejournal. 
Today has been a shitty day overall. SOmetimes I feel like "hey ASU isn't so bad, I could grow to like it here" Other times, like today, I feel like there is no one I can relate to. Talking about boys or listening to girls talking about getting drunk is only tolerable for so long. Everyone seems to come from money, those who don't pretend like they do. It's rush week at the sororities so the whole campus is a-buss. Gag me. It feels like in Tempe, it's a sea of lame-os and you have to search for the quality people. In tucson I think it was more cool people but you could definitely find the snobs if you wanted to. So....i just wish I could find more people to relate to...
It feels like there are a few people in every class that I dont mind talking to for an hour, but no one I would consider a friend. Well, except Jenette. she's probably the closest person to me of the new people i've met. :)
I have my first exam tomorrow....bleh. I dont feel too ready but I'll be ok...especially since he drops your lowest exam score. 
I had my dance class tonight.,..i missed last week so I had a lot of catching up. It's a lot of fun though, i think with practice I'll get pretty goood.
Anyway, I'm off. I need to go study.

It's not bad up here, actually. I've met a few really cool people that I now consider friends. Including my roomate! She's a really great girl..I don't think we'll be hanging out outside the room too often, but we sit around and chat often. So, whats new in the land of Barbie? Nothing much. College is nothing like I expected..well, i guess it is...it just seems stupid that teachers in High school ran things in one way.. and BAM! now in college it's just read the text, come to lectures, and take tests. that's it. I feel like {atleast in my intro classes} I could just buy books and teach myself. I guess gen eds just suck, it gets better though right guys? 
BUT! I AM SELF SUFFICIENT! I did my own laundry yesterday { a special moment, the first college laundry trip} AND! I hunted all over campus till someone would help me fix my computer, they told me what to do...and now it's all fixed!! ASU's ethernet system is wicked fast and awesome, but also a bitch.
i feel very stressed out, lots of stuff to do ALL THE TIME. I miss everyone alot too...
Robert and I are having a tough time with the distance right now. it's tough having a girlfriend far away wwith a biggillion guys, and i understand that. I just know how faithful and dedicated I am to him and I can't wait until there isn't this adjustment and tension anymore. I love him so much.
ok, i'm off to work on homework. love yall!

So, i'm at college! 
I'm almost unpacked...i've kinda been procrastinating on putting the clothes away...But, the computer is up and so is the tv and fridge {lord knows the food better be there for me at all times!]
Moving in yesterday was very tough for me...I cried a lot. Partly because I only got 2 hours of sleep and we all know how emotional that can make people. Also because i'm PMSing...Mostly because I'm REALLY missing my family, boyfriend, and friends..I know I'm gonna make more friends...my roomate is a really sweet girl and I get along with my suitemates, but I still feel alittle lonely. Rich and Amanda have been spending a good amount of time with me which I really appreciate. Mostly I've been focusing on getting all my stuff settled for classes on monday;I think once classes start and i'm more involved, I won't feel as lonely. I'm just not a big fan of getting all dressed up and going to mixers and BBQs all weekend.
BUT!!! I Am excited because I'm looking for my work study job and I spoke to a guy in the theatre department, appearantly they are hiring students to work as techies for the year! So, we talked shop for awhile and he even spoke to me about auditioning for the upcoming show. I think i'm gonna do it...not cuz i'll get cast, but atleast for the experience.
So...thats all for now. I miss you all so much! please comment....

I'm sorry i've been so neglectful, but not having a working computer at my house has made stuff difficult. I love my Dell though {which is stashed at gramm's so the baby doesn't destroy it} and I've been putting pics on it {cuz it's fast enough to do that! MUhahah!}
I fucking hate ASU FINANCIAL AID DEPARTMENT!
